# Contact modal wiring - preserve on every edit

The slatepress.co homepage uses a critical contact-modal pattern. Several wires are easy to break when redesigning the hero or any CTA. The contact form is the funnel entrance - breaking these wires means prospects can't reach it.

## Required HTML attributes

- Every CTA button intended to open the contact modal MUST have a `data-contact-modal` attribute.
- The launch film section requires `id="filmVideo"` on the video element and `id="filmPoster"` on the poster fallback image.

## Required script reference

- `<script src="assets/contact-modal.js"></script>` MUST be present in the page, typically near the closing `</body>` tag.

## What can break it

- Hero redesigns that replace CTAs with new buttons but forget the `data-contact-modal` attribute.
- "Cleanup" passes that remove what look like unused script tags.
- Renaming the film video element IDs when changing the video.

## Verification after any index.html edit

Run these greps before committing:

```
grep -c "data-contact-modal" index.html  # should match the number of contact CTAs
grep "contact-modal.js" index.html       # should return one line
grep "filmVideo\|filmPoster" index.html  # should return both IDs
```

If any of these go to zero, the contact funnel is broken. Fix before pushing.
